Day 1: Python Basics
🎯 Focus

Variables, input handling, and data types

📌 Concepts Learned
Variables store values in memory (name = "Sudhu")
Python is dynamically typed (no need to declare type)
input() always returns a string
Common data types:
int → whole numbers
float → decimals
str → text
bool → True/False
[[[[[[💻 Practice Code
name = input("Enter your name: ")
age = int(input("Enter your age: "))
height = float(input("Enter your height: "))

print("Name:", name)
print("Age:", age)
print("Height:", height)]]]]]]
⚠️ Key Mistake I faced
input() returns string, so math doesn’t work without conversion
🔧 Fix
Used int() and float() to convert input properly
🚀 Result
Successfully stored and displayed user data using correct data types
